<BaseLayout pageTitle="Test of Flourish & Dropcap">
  <main id="main">
    <section class="container stack">
      <div class="wrap w-100">
        <h3>Dropcap</h3>
        <Flourish classes={['--alder', 'dropcap', '--dc-brand-purple-dk bt']}>
          <p>
            The Flourish component works hand-in-hand with <code>.dropcap</code>
            class to dropcap the first letter in a block of text. To use it add the
            <code>.dropcap</code> class to the parent block containing text. <i
              >Note:</i
            > The text needs to also be wrapped in a <code>&#x3C;p&#x3E;</code> tag.
          </p>
        </Flourish>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="container stack">
      <div class="wrap w-100">
        <h3>Dropcap Classes</h3>
        <p class="bt">
          <code>.dropcap</code> also has a set of CSS custom properties that are
          a subset of our brand colors. These are prefixed
          <code>--dc-color-name</code>, and can be used to add color to your
          drop cap charecter.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="container stack">
      <div class="wrap w-100">
        <h3>Flourish Use</h3>
        <p class="bt">
          Flourish classes are passed into the the Flourish component as an
          array.
        </p>
        <pre><code>&lt;Flourish
  classes=&#x7b;['--rowan-leaves', 'dropcap', '--dc-brand-purple-dk']&#x7d;&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Some text...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/Flourish&gt;</code></pre>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="container stack">
      <div class="wrap w-100">
        <h3>Flourish Properties</h3>
        <div class="grid-ns grid-cols-3 bt">
          <ul class="list f7">
            <li><code>--alder</code></li>
            <li><code>--apple</code></li>
            <li><code>--aspen</code></li>
            <li><code>--beech</code></li>
            <li><code>--downybirch</code></li>
